news.title: Bring all commercial & residential properties in Delhi under tax net: LG to MCD
news.para: ​In a review meeting on Friday, the LG also directed the Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) to make all its services related to property tax filing, mutation and building plan sanction among others IT-enabled by July 31.

news.title: Complete TOD project before scheduled deadline: Delhi LG to DDA, NBCC
news.para: ​He had gone to take stock of the status and progress of work at the site of the project in east Delhi, according to the statement issued by the Raj Niwas.

news.title: Blackstone’s Nucleus Office Parks invests over Rs 100 crore in properties’ ESG upgrade
news.para: The operating platform houses 20 million sq ft office spaces across its 18 assets in top five property markets of the country including Mumbai, Bangalore, NCR, Chennai and Ahmedabad.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes four dilapidated buildings
news.para: Officials concerned were instructed to identify and demolish old and dilapidated structures that could collapse during rainy season and lead to an accident, IMC deputy commissioner Lata Agrawal said.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM distributes rural residential rights documents to 11 lakh families
news.para: At a function organised in the auditorium of Lok Bhawan, Adityanath distributed the documents and stressed on making a self-reliant state.

news.title: Noida: RWA federation wants fees for property transfer to kin waived
news.para: The move comes after the state government on June 15 provided relief to property owners on transfer to blood relations for a fee of Rs 6,000, as against the 7% stamp registration duty earlier.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust asks Atal flat allottees to surrender extra allotment
news.para: LIT executive officer Kuljit Kaur said the allottees have to tender the affidavits on Rs 100 stamp paper duly attested by the magistrate that they did not get more than one flat to the names of their spouse and dependent children.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 127 units in three commercial buildings
news.para: Officials said that despite multiple notices and reminders, the property owners failed to renew their fire safety no objection certificates (NOC).

news.title: Only 17% owners in Prayagraj clear their house tax dues
news.para: PMC authorities have served notices to over 15,000 house owners who have not deposited their house tax for the past five years or more with an appeal to clear the pending house tax dues or face strict measures.

news.title: Secunderabad Cantonment to unveil unified tax for property
news.para: ​Currently, 62 Cantonments across the country are following different methods for calculation of annual rateable value (ARV) of properties and as a result, many Cantonments, including Secunderabad Cantonment, are earning poor revenues through annual property tax.

news.title: Kanpur civic body identifies 48,368 new properties to assess tax
news.para: The verification work has been completed, and KMC will realize Rs 35 crore as house tax from those property owners.

news.title: Delhi: RWAs' body raises concerns over property tax portal
news.para: In a letter written to the commissioner and the assessor and collector (property tax) on Friday, URJA claimed that the previous receipts for the amount paid by cheque in property tax camps were still not available on the corporation’s portal.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board 's 13 facilities will be a click away from July 1
news.para: No application through physical mode will be accepted from the day. This will help the applicants to apply online from their homes and get services on time without visiting the CHB office.

news.title: GDA wants Ghaziabad civic body to take over Raj Nagar Extension
news.para: The move, if implemented, would be similar to the partial takeover of Indirapuram by the corporation. It was in a meeting convened to discuss issues holding up the handover of Indirapuram that the GDA made the proposal for Raj Nagar Extension.

news.title: Over 122 lakh houses sanctioned so far under PMAY-Urban: Government
news.para: In a statement, the Union Housing and Urban Affairs Ministry said that more than 1 crore houses have been grounded and over 61 lakh houses completed and delivered to the beneficiaries. At a virtual event, HUA Secretary Manoj Joshi urged states and union territories to expedite construction work in their respective regions to fulfil the target of "Housing for All".
